  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Regulatory requirement FR-HEM-001 mandates that hemolysis predictions for Class II CPB devices meet a relative hemolysis index acceptance criterion of RH < 1 against a predicate device; this requirement is documented inline within the package evidence body but is not formally bound at the UnitOfAssurance level.",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
